<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The &quot;only in groups of 3 to 6&quot; seems like quite an artificial limit. I don't see how it can be explained through any form of spell design that fits in with the game world. I don't see what it saves either. Aggro is now the same, regardless of how far away you are from the mob. Make the spell line melee-range and make that one of the tradeoffs you must endure in exchange for its higher ratios.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Bard songs?  How about charms?  Lots of things in the game don't make sense for the type of game it is, I could sit here and name literally thousands... but that would go nowhere. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
Easy &quot;roleplaying&quot; reasoning!  You're drawing the power of your allies to smite your foes.  To few and you cannot evoke a powerful enough spell to do any damage... to many and you get overwhelmed.<br>
<br>
Oh, aggro isn't that large of an issue in EXP groups provided you actually use the tools given to you to manage it.  I rarely have issues keeping aggro off me (no Greater Concussion either) even when I've joined groups with the crappiest Warrior you could ever imagine (with both of my Wizards).  Simple solution, give it a lower aggro multiplier than another spell.  Like I said, the example above was just an example. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=myztic>MyztiC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>Born-Again Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 896<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/29/03 11:59:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26302.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> Even though adding the flappy 100% to the group could be too powerful, if it weren't all classes would have similar. Then a possible solution would be to add 50% of flappy effects to the group. Even then it would be a nice addition in higher levels, but then again, do nothing at lower levels. Then again, the lower level flappies wouldn't probably help even if the effect was added 100% to the whole group.<br>
