<br>
I'm in favor of melee-range 'touch' spells with a high mana efficiency and high level of damage.  Heck, why not actually offer this for all current spells?  If you are in melee range when you begin casting the spell, and are still in melee range when the spell lands, reduce the mana cost for the spell by 33% and add a small Concussion (hate-reduction) component that reduces the hate of the spell by 33%.  Keep the damage and casting time the same.  This would increase the overall damage we could do in groups without affecting our soloing abilities.<br>
<br>
-Raystonn<br>
