r offensive aas compared to wizards. I think, then, that your dps improves in comparison to the melees whenever their attack is off and the more you're buffed. the 'evac benefit' in POP is considerably less with easily accessable Zoneouts and graveyards. I think you can always get 'good' xp(provided no crowding) comparable to inacessable zoneouts just in different zones. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=phlixarcanist>Phlix Arcanist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/29/03 10:08:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26302.topic&index=49>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hm</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The one decent suggestion I've seen in these threads would be to make our flappy to affect whole group. That would simply be awesome. The 8pt stackable regen and manapool boost is something shamans/clerics would like a lot and then even non-social and rude wizards would be wanted to groups. And it wouldn't cause us to buff any more than usual, the 7 hours on flappy is awesome duration.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
